<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" http-equiv="Content-Type" />
    <style>
      body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; }
      .container { max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }
      .header { background-color: #dc3545; color: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 5px 5px 0 0; }
      .content { background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; }
      .footer { margin-top: 20px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-size: 12px; color: #6c757d; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="header">
        <h1>ðŸš¨ Critical System Alert</h1>
      </div>
      
      <div class="content">
        <p>This is a critical system alert.</p>
        
        <p>No super admin user exists in the system. Product imports and many administrative functions require a super admin to be configured.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Action Required:</strong></p>
        
        <p>Please create a super admin user immediately by running the following command:</p>
        
        <pre style="background: #f4f4f4; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px; overflow-x: auto;">
Rails.application.credentials.super_admin_email = "your-email@example.com"
        </pre>
        
        <p>Or use the Rails console to designate an existing user as super admin:</p>
        
        <pre style="background: #f4f4f4; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px; overflow-x: auto;">
user = User.find_by(email: "your-email@example.com")
user.update!(role: "super_admin")
        </pre>
        
        <div class="footer">
          <p>This is an automated message from SupplierHub.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
